docs.text: now she makes her directorial debut , writing , directing , and starring in this sub-par film about women talking about sex .

docs.text: though not without redeeming qualities , this film is bad .

docs.text: the basic story follows three single friends -- jazz ( beyer ) , lena ( randi ingerman ) , and michelle ( paget brewster ) -- in their search for love .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: jazz has an idea for a local talk show ; it would feature women talking about sex and dating .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: she and her friends make a demo tape of interviews with the women of miami .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the film itself is sprinkled with these real interviews throughout , both as part of the plot and as commentary on the situations of the main characters .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the fact that they are real provides a refreshing break from some of the more melodramatic moments in the film .

docs.text: there are several moments of bad acting , corny dialogue , and emotional overextension .

docs.text: in a low-budget independent film from a first-time director , these faults can sometimes be forgiven , if the screenplay is fresh and solid .

docs.text: taken together , they form a mosaic picture of miami beachwalkers and bistro diners .

docs.text: the mosaic is made of sound bites and stereotypes , but each tile is some woman's real experience .

docs.text: neither the picture of women , nor their picture of men , is truly representative , but the point is that both sets of generalizations are telling in their own way .
